Set scheduling parameter of a child thread:

    pthread_attr_t attr;
    pthread_attr_init(&attr);

    // setting up pthread_attr_t structure

    // Create the child thread
    pthread_create(&tid, &attr, &func, &arg);


Inheriting from parent's scheduling parameters (priority and algorithm):
    pthread_attr_setinheritsched(&attr, PTHREAD_INHERIT_SCHED);
    // same as
    // pthread_create(NULL, NULL, func, arg);


Setting scheduling parameters explicitly:
    struct sched_param param;
    pthread_attr_setinheritsched(&attr, PTHREAD_EXPLICIT_SCHED);

Set scheduling priority:
    param.sched_priority = 15;
    pthread_attr_setschedparam(&attr, &param);

Set scheduling policy:
    pthread_attr_setschedpolicy(&attr, policy);

policy are int with predefined values: SCHED_FIFO, SCHED_RR and others.



Modifying the scheduling parameters of an existing thread (in the same process):

    struct sched_param param;
    param.sched_priority = new_priority;
    pthread_setschedparam(tid, policy, &param);

    // To modify itself, use pthread_self() for tid.


To get the current scheduling parameters:

    pthread_getschedparam(tid, &policy, &param);


--------------

SCHED_FIFO: 1, priority 1 to 63
SCHED_RR: 2, priority 1 to 63
